        "filename": "apps/plugins/xrick/system/sysarg_rockbox.c",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 39,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000430
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-10-08T23:58:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m just reusing what the original xrick code provides here. Considering that the macro is already available, don\u0027t think there is any harm in reusing it, plus I think it\u0027s more readable than the usual \"(void) variable\" construct.\n\nAs a side note: the SDL (Windows/Linux/Mac) version of xrick generates a warnings on non-gnu compilers (due to UNUSED not being defined for them -it boils down to a compiler specific extension-), so I\u0027ll probably have to add the \"(void) variable\" construct regardless under SDL.\nHowever we know the rockbox port is compiled under gcc, so I\u0027m planning to leave it as it is for better clarity, unless you have strong opinions against it... ;)",
      "parentUuid": "5a18252c_15e4940b",
      "revId": "c2fbc38b349f062ea61f5c7691fc0551f627953f",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": false
