      "writtenOn": "2014-10-08T23:58:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "in this specific case we can sleep for a (relatively) long time because the game is paused: nothing apart from button polling gets done.\nSo yes, I could use it, but line 73 still needs the normal (non-PLA) button polling, because it turns out PLA is not working for me when game running.\nNot sure why, but I think the PLA code is not fast enough to be able to detect button changes when a very busy loop involved, also I can\u0027t block main game loop for too long (when game not paused) because I need to perform sound mixing, video update etc, moreover it looks like PLA is doing a lot of things which can make the code run (unnecessarily) slower.\n\nDo you know if PLA can be used at all when busy loops involved?",
      "parentUuid": "5a18252c_d55cdcef",
      "revId": "c2fbc38b349f062ea61f5c7691fc0551f627953f",
